# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# fourth-kernel.form — the sibling whose source is Form: native artifacts
#                      emitted from recipes, measured against the three walkers
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Urs: "I would love to have a native BMF compiler and a native API host binary
# just to compare them performance, memory footprint, etc. and I would love to
# have a host-kernel native cli written from the form recipe instead of
# go/rust/TS as fourth kernel to compare against."
#
# This is kernel-self-composition's close-self-rebuild-loop choosing its first
# stones, and host-kernel's zero-to-many-implementations made literal: a FOURTH
# carrier of the same content-addressed body, whose source is not a host
# language a human wrote but text the recipes themselves emit. The comparison
# is the point — champion-challenger discipline over real measured rows (wall
# time, maximum RSS, binary size, startup), never a claim of superiority.
# Each artifact earns its place by counts, and the walkers stay authoritative
# for semantics: the emitted native must return the walker's values.
#
# Two emission lanes exist today; this spec names them honestly:
#   kernel-resident lowering — jit_emit_c / jit.go: the kernel lowers a recipe
#     to C/native. General (handles recursion), RUNS, but the lowerer is
#     host-language hardcode. A bridge carrier, and itself M4's lift target.
#   emitter-as-recipe — jit-tensor-emit.fk, fourth-kernel-emit.fk: the emitter
#     IS Form; the kernel keeps dumb carriers (clang/rustc, dlopen/exec). The
#     body-owned lane this spec grows. close-jit-crystallization's heart.

(fourth-kernel

  (lineage
    (closes-toward  kernel-self-composition.close-self-rebuild-loop)  # author -> compile -> boot bigger
    (heart-of       host-kernel.close-jit-crystallization)            # recipe -> native, installed, meltable
    (lane-proven    jit-tensor-emit.fk)                               # the emitter as Form, bit-for-bit, 20077x
    (carrier-rule   host-kernel.host-resource-access)                 # clang/rustc/loader: allowed carriers
    (measures-like  champion-challenger.fk recognition-router.fk)     # earned flips, measured fitness
    (coordinates    codex/native-http-stack-architecture)             # the API-host slice shares that seam
    (seed           fourth-kernel-emit.fk tests/fourth-kernel-emit-band.fk
                    scripts/fourth_kernel_audit.sh))

  # ── The measurement protocol (shared by every milestone) ─────────────
  # A row is honest when the SAME semantic ask runs through each carrier's
  # own front door, values agree, and the numbers carry their conditions.
  (measurement-protocol
    (ask          identical-recipe-semantics-per-carrier)   # e.g. fib 28 = 317811 everywhere
    (parity-first values-must-agree-before-any-timing-counts)
    (rows         wall-time maximum-rss binary-size startup-time)
    (carriers     form-kernel-go form-kernel-rust form-kernel-ts the-emitted-native)
    (conditions   named-with-every-number)                  # machine, flags, N, date
    (evidence     docs/system_audit/commit_evidence-records)
    (observability a-carrier-without-a-probe-door-is-not-yet-a-sibling)  # trace arms +
                  # framebuffer provenance ride every milestone; the walker-as-recipes
                  # inherits the kernels' Blueprint attribution for free (measured:
                  # fib(10)-as-data = 14,360 WITNESS + 8,562 ACCESS + 5,738 COND vs
                  # 264 MATH — the meta-interpretation tax made visible, ~87 dispatches
                  # per real op, exactly what m4c's emitter collapses); the EMITTED
                  # lane is dark today (fk4 has no probe) — m4c carries its probe out
    (verdict      champion-challenger-earned-never-declared))

  # ── M1 — the CLI seed [SHIPPED with this spec] ────────────────────────
  # A complete standalone C program — integer printer, fib, sum, ackermann,
  # argv main — every byte emitted by Form recipes (fourth-kernel-emit.fk),
  # one quoteless line (extern declarations instead of #include: preprocessor
  # lines need newlines, a Form string is one line — the constraint shaped a
  # cleaner emission). Proven three-way: the program text is byte-identical
  # across kernels and prefix-parameterized (band → 7). The audit script
  # carries the text through clang, checks value parity against the walkers,
  # and writes the first measured comparison rows.
  (m1-cli-seed
    (emitter      fourth-kernel-emit.fk)                    # fk4-program: the whole binary as a string
    (proof        tests/fourth-kernel-emit-band.fk -> 7 three-way)
    (carrier      scripts/fourth_kernel_audit.sh)           # clang -O2, parity, time/rss/size/startup
    (workloads    fib sum ackermann)                        # the kernels/README.md performance frame
    (lowering     recursion-to-loops-for-fib-and-sum ack-stays-recursive)  # value parity over integers
    (next         emit-from-recipe-shape-not-hand-shaped-text))  # walk the recipe tree to C, in Form

  # ── M2 — the native BMF compiler ──────────────────────────────────────
  # The BMF engine (apply-object-rule, engine.fk; the BML compiler picture in
  # kernels/BMF_BML_COMPILER_PICTURE.md) emitted as a native binary: source in,
  # recipes out. Compared against the three kernels compiling the same BML
  # corpus: compile throughput, RSS, startup. The .fkb bootstrap-image ratchet
  # is the natural exchange format — the native compiler proves itself by
  # producing the same content-addressed image the walkers produce.
  (m2-bmf-compiler-native
    (compose      engine.fk-rule-application                # runs three-way today
                  fourth-kernel-emit-lane                   # the emitter discipline from M1
                  fkb-image-as-parity-gate)                 # same source -> same NodeIDs -> same image
    (proof        a-band-where-native-and-walker-compile-one-corpus-to-equal-images)
    (verification-source primitive-registry.fk)             # the natives it carries, answered entry-by-entry
    (rows         compile-throughput rss startup binary-size)
    # ── Proof-of-shape SHIPPED: grammar + source -> a new binary, grammar-driven ──
    (proof-of-shape bmf-mini.fk)                            # rules-as-cells (token, op, operand)
    (transform    grammar-and-source-cells-folded-into-a-program-as-cells)  # the compiler-compiler kernel
    (grammar-is-data  swap-the-grammar-get-a-different-binary)  # proven in COMPILED output
    (pipeline     compile-recipe -> fkc-emit-many -> clang -> a-running-binary)  # end to end, in the audit
    (band         tests/bmf-mini-band.fk -> 15 three-way)   # faithful vs reference, grammar-is-data, program-as-cell
    (witnessed    "g1 tok1=ADD10 -> binary -> 22 ; g2 tok1=ADD100 -> binary -> 202, same source [1,1,2]")
    (honest-scope tokenwise-pattern-action-fold)            # the nesting/choose/fail engine is m4e3
    (compiler-as-recipe-today  the-compiler-folds-Form-lists)  # heap now has a native arena
    (compiler-as-binary-needs  m4e4-strings + m4e3-real-recipe-flattener)  # textual source/full engine, named

    # ── The BMF discipline (Urs, 2026-06-11) — bmf-architecture.form's record ──
    # BMF is NOT tokenize-then-parse. Rules match bytes STRAIGHT OFF a streaming
    # CURSOR over the source ("Run — what a lexer would scan, inline ... no
    # lexer, no token stream"); backtracking restores a CURSOR POSITION and a
    # STACK COORDINATE — both pointer moves, O(1), axiom-3's gift. Recipe args
    # and locals ride the STACK, never heap environments. bmf-mini's tokenwise
    # fold proved the grammar-as-data transform only — it pre-tokenized, which
    # is NOT the BMF parse shape; the cursor lane below is.
    (bmf-discipline
      (streaming-cursor   bytes-straight-off-the-source no-lexer-no-token-stream)
      (backtrack          restore-cursor-position-and-stack-mark both-pointer-moves)
      (stack-not-heap     recipe-args-and-locals-ride-the-call-stack)
      (cursor-lane-SHIPPED op-17-BUF reads the loaded source stream; the cursor
                          position lives in the RAM organ so save/restore IS
                          SET/GET — a pointer move; witnessed in the audit:
                          one matcher table, source x42 -> rule A matches off
                          the cursor -> 42; source 9001 -> A fails on byte one
                          -> cursor RESTORED -> rule B streams digits -> 9001;
                          args on the C call stack throughout)
      (fail-honesty       fail-as-0 collides with a matched 0 — BMF's richer
                          ack vocabulary {nothing,0,1,node} is the named fix
                          when the walker grows a nothing value)))

  # ── M3 — the native API host ──────────────────────────────────────────
  # The front door as one native binary: socket accept, HTTP parse, route
  # dispatch over the BML catalog shapes (kernel-http.fk, http-serve.fk,
  # production-routes.fk, api.bml), JSON emit. Measured against form-kernel-go
  # serve on the same routes: p50/p95, RSS, startup, binary size. This slice
  # shares a seam with the native-http-stack architecture work (codex branch);
  # the offered interface is the meeting point, not a race.
  (m3-api-host-native
    (compose      kernel-http.fk http-serve.fk production-routes-shapes
                  fourth-kernel-emit-lane)
    (parity       X-Form-Router-receipts-and-body-equality-against-the-go-front-door)
    (rows         p50 p95 rss startup binary-size)
    (coordinate   codex-native-http-stack-architecture))

  # ── M4 — the walker itself (the true fourth sibling) ──────────────────
  # The emitter grows from hand-shaped program text (M1) to walking a recipe
  # tree and emitting its lowering — the lowerer as recipe, jit_emit_c's
  # intelligence moved into the body. Then the emitted program IS a kernel:
  # intern, node_eq, category dispatch over a primitive subset, enough to
  # realize a chosen band family. That binary joins validate.sh as the fourth
  # arm, and close-self-rebuild-loop's band cites this lane: a kernel authors,
  # compiles, and boots a strictly larger kernel.
  (m4-walker-emitted
    (compose      recipe-tree-walk-in-form                  # the lowerer as recipe
                  intern-and-node-eq-emission               # the substrate spine, emitted
                  validate.sh-fourth-arm)                   # sibling parity includes the emitted one
    (closes       kernel-self-composition.close-self-rebuild-loop)
    (question-list primitive-registry.fk)                   # declares its subset, answers each entry's
                                                            # verification recipe with the declared outside
    (proof        the-emitted-kernel-passes-a-named-band-family-and-its-values-equal-the-three)

    # The bootstrap ladder (Urs named it; the order is what makes it safe —
    # the fourth kernel is CORRECT before it is FAST, proven by the same bands):
    (ladder
      (m4a-surface     name minimal-kernel.form's four families as ONE recipe-
                       callable door each (a minimal-surface cell + band); prove
                       all kernels agree through the doors — after this band,
                       a recipe against the surface runs identically everywhere
                       [SHIPPED: form-stdlib/minimal-surface.fk +
                       tests/minimal-surface-band.fk -> 31, three-way —
                       intern/observe/offer/port one door each; the BMF
                       thread/choice lane and the axiom-3 save/restore gift
                       proven as their own claims; MS-PAIR registered
                       1.2.99.1300])
      (m4b-walker-as-recipes  the fourth kernel authored as recipes over the
                       surface, run INTERPRETED on the existing kernels first;
                       form-engine.form already proves the walk loop is
                       recipe-expressible — 15/15 dispatch arms
                       [FIRST WALKER SHIPPED: form-stdlib/fourth-walker.fk +
                       tests/fourth-walker-band.fk -> 15, three-way — programs
                       are content-addressed cells built through the intern
                       door (same program twice = same cell, one leaf changed
                       = different cell); dispatch-on-tag down the observe
                       door; LIT/ARG/ADD/SUB/LE/IF/SELF; fib authored as data
                       answers 55 through SELF re-entering the program; the
                       walker touches only surface doors + figure leaves.
                       Open here: the op set grows toward the full category
                       table as m4c's emitter learns to lower it])
      (m4c-emit-and-boot  the emitter recipe (this file's lane, generalized
                       from hand-shaped text to walking the recipe tree) emits
                       the walker's native source; the toolchain port compiles;
                       the binary boots and joins validate.sh as the fourth arm
                       — AND emits its probe with it: arm counters and NodeID
                       provenance in the emitted source, read through the port
                       door; the sibling must not go dark as it gets fast
                       [FIRST BOOT SHIPPED: fourth-walker-emit.fk +
                       tests/fourth-walker-emit-band.fk -> 15, three-way —
                       the emitter READS the program cells (post-order flatten
                       incl. the 3-child IF), the table + root vary while the
                       walker text stays program-independent, the full C
                       byte-exact. The audit boots it: fib-as-cells -> clang
                       -> fkw, parity 317811, THE PROBE INSIDE (fk_arms self-
                       reported 9.2M dispatches by tag), fib 28 in 16.9 ms /
                       1.3 MB / 33 KB vs the siblings' 450-1742 ms on the same
                       program-as-data — the meta-tax collapsed ~27-100x with
                       the trace riding. Open here: validate.sh fourth-arm
                       wiring, NodeID provenance plane, and m4d's self-emission
                       (the op set needs string/emit ops to run the emitter)])
      (m4d-fixpoint    the booted kernel re-runs the SAME emitter recipe on
                       itself: same content-address in, byte-identical source
                       out — self-hosting, close-self-rebuild-loop's band
                       stated plainly
                       [QUINE SEED SHIPPED — the data half: four ops grew the
                       walker, each an axiom-face (8 NODE = observe-itself,
                       9 PUTC = the efferent port, 10/11 DIV/MOD = figure
                       leaves; PUTC returns 0 so ADD sequences); the
                       self-printer walks its OWN node table and emits it
                       byte-exactly — 283 rows, 3388 bytes, the probe
                       narrating from inside: PUTC count == byte count, SELF
                       284 = rows+1, NODE 3176 self-reads. The quine knot (a
                       program containing its own true length) closes by
                       fixpoint authoring — row count is independent of the
                       literal, one rebuild lands it (fkd-self-printer).
                       Band tests/fourth-fixpoint-band.fk -> 15 three-way;
                       the byte-exact check lives in the audit. Remaining
                       for the FULL fixpoint: stream the constant walker
                       text (a string-pool lane), then the emitter itself
                       authored as a program — self-hosting whole])
      (leaf-honesty    the four leaf implementations (intern's hashing, the
                       trampoline, dlopen/exec ports) are the only genuinely
                       per-host native part — emitted from canonical
                       implementation-recipes, verified against laws-as-bands,
                       native by definition: they are what native MEANS)

      # ── m4e — the north star: the existing kernel surface, fully present ──
      # Urs: the fourth kernel carries what the three siblings carry. The
      # RATCHET is the band suite: every stone is measured as stdlib bands
      # runnable on the fourth arm (424 bands today; fkw runs 0 real bands —
      # its programs are combinator-authored). The walk, in surface order:
      (m4e-surface-walk
        (ratchet     bands-passing-on-fkw-over-424)         # the measure, never a claim
        (m4e1-call   CALL + a function table: one-param functions called by
                     index — kills the SELF single-recursion limit, lands
                     mutual recursion, AND unblocks the emitter-as-program
                     (the full m4d fixpoint's named blocker)
                     [SHIPPED: fk-call + fkm-walk/fkm-run (recipe side, SELF
                     re-grounded as re-enter fn 0 — single-function programs
                     walk unchanged) + fkc-flatten-many/fkc-emit-many (one
                     table, fk_fn[] roots, CALL dispatches through it);
                     tests/fourth-call-band.fk -> 15 three-way (even/odd
                     mutual recursion, fib-via-CALL = 55 + SELF back-compat,
                     the 18-row two-function table with roots 8,17,
                     deterministic emission); audit boots it: even(10)=1
                     even(7)=0, fib-via-CALL(28)=317811 at 19.3 ms — the
                     CALL indirection priced against the SELF shape])
        (m4e2-heap   lists as an arena heap in the emitted C: cons/head/
                     tail/len/nth/empty — the band subset's structural half
                     [SHIPPED: tag 17 remains BUF for the streaming BMF
                     cursor; tags 18..23 are EMPTY/CONS/HEAD/TAIL/LEN/NTH.
                     The emitted C carries fk_heap_head/fk_heap_tail beside
                     fk_src; tests/fourth-heap-band.fk -> 15 three-way; the
                     audit loads a heap table through the universal binary
                     and gets 25 from head([7,8]) + head(tail([7,8])) +
                     len([7,8]) + nth([7,8],1)]
                     # Two heaps were laid in parallel this hour — first
                     # merged won; the other composted into these honesties:
                     (ack-gap-open  EMPTY returns 0, so empty-list, a matched
                                    0, and BMF fail share one value — axiom-1's
                                    NOTHING still has no first-class carrier in
                                    the sibling; {nothing, 0, 1, node} completes
                                    when absence gets a nonzero sentinel reached
                                    through an OP, or a tagged ABI)
                     # Urs asked: could NIL/NULL be encoded AS nothing? Yes —
                     # and the axioms say it is the CORRECT encoding, on one
                     # condition: refs and ints must be distinguishable.
                     (ack-encoding-answer
                       (one-bit-tag   refs odd — ref(idx) = idx<<1|1; ints even — v<<1)
                       (nothing-is    the-null-reference = 1)   # ref-space zero
                       (then          NIL NULL empty-list BMF-fail timeout are ONE
                                      ground state — axiom-1's nothing, first-class)
                       (int-0-honest  a matched zero is data, never a fail)
                       (node-is       any non-null ref — a counter-offer IS a cell ref)
                       (the-gift      the ack vocabulary {nothing, 0, 1, node} IS the
                                      value type system: {null-ref, int-zero, int-one,
                                      ref} — protocol and ABI are one shape)
                       (behaviors     CHOICE pops on nothing; IF branches on zero —
                                      fail and false finally distinct, both expressible)
                       (cost          one shift per op — priced by the audit rows,
                                      champion-challenger against the sentinel design)
                       (lands-at      m4e3 alongside the real-recipe flattener)
                       (SHIPPED       the multi-function + universal + jit lanes now
                                      speak the tagged ABI: table raw, LIT encodes on
                                      read (<<1), refs odd, EMPTY = 1 = the null ref =
                                      NOTHING; witnessed — matched-0 -> 0, no-match ->
                                      1, distinct through plain IF, no sentinel; every
                                      prior parity unchanged (fib 317811, heap 25,
                                      bmf 22/202, organs 7, jit flip, quine byte-exact
                                      on the raw single lane); the os-band caught the
                                      lowering change honestly ((2 + a): literals
                                      lower encoded) and bands re-pinned 4327/4242))
                     (range-honesty program literals ride intern_trivial_int,
                                    which is 32-BIT — larger literals truncate
                                    silently (a sentinel literal cost an
                                    infinite walk to discover); sentinels must
                                    be ops, never literals, until the tagged ABI)
                     (recipes-vs-natives len/nth landed native; the
                                    minimal-kernel discipline prefers walked
                                    recipes over head/tail — a champion-
                                    challenger question for m4e3, decided by
                                    counts, not churn))
        # ── THE OVERNIGHT WORK ORDER (Urs, 2026-06-11, going to bed) ──────
        # "work towards the current kernel surface fully implemented in the
        # 4th kernel and passing all bands; bonus: real binary/assembly
        # execution on all host resources; TTS and STT with the largest
        # public models; the largest LLM this Mac runs; the api served on a
        # binary compiled by the 4th kernel" — honest ladder, each stone
        # shipped + witnessed separately; any cell may pick up the next one:
        (overnight-ladder
          (n1-net-organ    [SHIPPED] socket/bind/listen/accept/fork own the
                           net organ in a server-variant main (fkc-emit-server,
                           quoteless externs); dup2(cfd,1) makes the PROGRAM's
                           PUTC bytes the response body; the request is drained
                           and the connection shut down cleanly. fkresp folds a
                           string into a PUTC-chain responder. tests/fourth-net-
                           band.fk -> 15 three-way)
          (n2-api-binary   [SHIPPED] a binary the 4th kernel compiled serves
                           HTTP 200 + JSON; the audit curls it live — GET
                           /health -> 200 sub-millisecond, three requests, the
                           fork-loop holding. THE api-on-a-4th-kernel-binary,
                           real. Next: read the request line off the cursor and
                           route (m4e3); JSON body from substrate values)
          (n3-driver       [SHIPPED] fkc-emit-driver: pipe/fork/execvp spawn
                           the argv-given command, its stdout captured into
                           fk_src, the PROGRAM parses that LIVE stream with the
                           BMF cursor. Witnessed: drive printf 31337 -> 31337,
                           drive date +%Y -> 2026 (the year off live date
                           stdout). tests/fourth-driver-band.fk -> 15 three-way.
                           THE keystone: TTS/STT/LLM are this organ + a parser)
          (n4-tts          [SHIPPED] the 4th-kernel binary (driver + fkcount)
                           drove /usr/bin/say -> 134642 bytes of real AIFF-C
                           audio. TTS physical through the sibling)
          (n5-stt          whisper-cpp not yet installed; the driver organ is
                           ready — brew whisper-cpp + large-v3, then fkcount
                           drives transcription and the cursor walks the
                           transcript. NAMED, organ proven (same shape as n4/n6))
          (n6-llm          [SHIPPED small + LARGEST in flight] the 4th-kernel
                           binary drove ollama llama3.2:3b and captured+counted
                           its real output bytes; the 115 GB dolphin-mixtral:
                           8x22b-q6_K (largest local, 128 GB RAM/16 cores) is
                           driven by the same binary — see the evidence record
                           for the measured load+generate. The organ driven,
                           never reimplemented (host-resource-access))
          (n7-ratchet      m4e3 flattener first click: ONE compiled .fk band
                           through the observe door onto the table; fkw runs
                           it; bands-on-fourth-arm 0 -> 1)
          (n8-assembly     otool -tv on emitted binaries in the audit — the
                           Form-emitted ARM64 assembly visible)
          (honesty         all-424-bands is a WALK not a night — families
                           climb as ops land (strings next); model COMPUTE
                           rides host organs by design — the sibling
                           orchestrates, ports, parses, measures))

        (m4e3-bridge the real-recipe flattener: read a COMPILED .fk recipe
                     through the observe door (node_category/node_children/
                     node_value) and flatten the REAL category set into the
                     table — fkw walks bands unmodified; validate.sh gains
                     the fourth arm for covered bands)
        (m4e4-grow   strings + str_eq, then natives family by family (the
                     minimal-kernel census order: figure, observe, intern,
                     port), each landing as bands flip to four-way)

        (m4e-universal  [SHIPPED] the UNIVERSAL walker — no baked program:
                     one emitted binary loads a node-table FILE through the
                     fs afferent port (open/read, quoteless extern decls)
                     and runs it. fkc-table-file serializes any program;
                     witnessed: ONE binary ran fib (317811), even/odd (1/0),
                     a bmf-grammar-compiled program (22), a heap program
                     (25), and the organ program (7) from five table files — load any source
                     that has a grammar, compile to cells, run, no rebuild)

        (m4e-jit     [SHIPPED] self-JIT on heat — learned-primitive's
                     crystallize in the emitted sibling: the emitter lowers
                     each pure function FROM ITS CELLS to a native C
                     alternative (fkc-nat-expr; ports/organs honestly not
                     lowered), the binary counts heat per function, and
                     dispatch flips to native when heat crosses the runtime
                     threshold. Witnessed: fib28 cold 19.3 ms walking ->
                     hot 3.0 ms after flipping at threshold 50, parity held,
                     njit=26 crossings in the probe — gas cooled to ice on
                     measured heat. Open, named: melt-on-cool, and true
                     runtime codegen for FOREIGN loaded tables (the universal
                     binary re-emitting through the toolchain port — the
                     full crystallization wire))

        (organs-physical  one physical proof per host resource through the
                     fourth sibling, band tests/fourth-os-band.fk -> 15:
                     (cpu     compute — every band and row)            # RUNS
                     (fs      the loader reads table files; PUTC emits) # RUNS
                     (ram     ops 13/14 SET/GET — write 42, read 42)   # RUNS
                     (clock   op 15 TIME — real epoch, positive)       # RUNS
                     (entropy op 16 RND — two draws differed)          # RUNS
                     (net hmi gpu — port-shaped, named for m4f; the
                      resource-port discipline holds their doors)))    # NAMED
      (hot-swap-free   the same emitter at runtime granularity: crystallize a
                       hot recipe -> toolchain port -> install by repoint ->
                       melt on cool, gated by champion-challenger counts))))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to verify (today)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   # M1 emission, three-way (the program text is the cell):
#   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/fourth-kernel-emit.fk \
#     form-stdlib/tests/fourth-kernel-emit-band.fk
#
#   # M1 carrier: compile the emitted text, prove value parity, measure rows:
#   scripts/fourth_kernel_audit.sh
#
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(fourth-kernel)"   # after ingest
